missionTeasers.title: Convenient Location and upscale amenities
missionTeasers.excerpt:
Meadow Ridge Pet Lodge﻿
2512 Marlin Drive, Rapid City, SD

Meadow Ridge Pet Lodge is your pets home away from home! An upscale experience for dogs and cats! Dog Daycare, training, upscale boarding with VIP suites, dog splash parks and a 16 beer & wine tap indoor / outdoor social area featuring theatre quality popcorn!

missionTeasers.title: Training
missionTeasers.excerpt: From puppy to pro - we have you covered with our amazing trainers!  Email training@meadowridgepetlodge.com for pricing and details!

missionTeasers.title: State-of-the-art Coffee Machine in our lobby
missionTeasers.excerpt:
At Meadow Ridge Pet Lodge, we believe every detail matters — for pets and their humans.

That’s why when you bring in your furry loved one, you’ll be welcomed by a state-of-the-art bean-to-cup coffee / iced-coffee or hot chocolate experience right in our lobby, featuring the Cafection Symbol coffee machine.

✨ Fresh-ground beans
✨ Café-quality drinks at the touch of a button
✨ Fast, smooth, and always consistent
And yes — pricing so reasonable even your dog will wag their tail about it. 

Whether it’s a quick morning drop-off or a moment to take a breath before heading out, we want you to start your day with something warm, familiar, and comforting — just like the care your pet receives inside.

Exceptional care. Thoughtful touches. A place where both pets and their humans feel at home.

missionTeasers.title: Upscale Boarding
missionTeasers.excerpt: Our upscale boarding experience goes beyond traditional kenneling by combining luxury accommodations with structured care and professional supervision. Pets enjoy spacious private suites, climate-controlled comfort, advanced air purification, and thoughtfully designed social and enrichment opportunities. Every stay includes attentive monitoring, individualized care routines, and a clean, secure environment built to reduce stress and promote well-being.

training.title: Basic Obedience Classes
training.description:
Upcoming Basic Obedience Classes:

Basic Obedience - April 13th at 6 PM 
Basic Obedience - April 29th at 5 PM

This class is a great way to work with your dog in a group environment. In this class, we will cover: sit, down, place, stay, loose leash walking, leave it, general manners, and more! These classes run for an hour, once a week, for 6 weeks. The cost is $165 plus tax for the entire class. 

To sign up, email training@meadowridgepetlodge.com

training.title: Puppy Obedience Classes
training.description:
Upcoming Puppy Obedience Classes:

Puppy Obedience - April 14th at 5 PM
Puppy Obedience - April 29th at 6 PM

This class is similar to our basic obedience class but is catered to puppies. In addition to learning obedience commands, your puppy will learn how to properly socialize with other dogs and puppies. We also cover crate training, potty training, and how to fix common problem behaviors. This class is great for growing confidence and learning how to raise a stable puppy. Your puppy must be at least 8 weeks old and no more than 6 months old at the beginning of class. These classes run for an hour, once a week, for 6 weeks. The cost is $165 plus tax for the entire class. 

To sign up, email training@meadowridgepetlodge.com

training.title: Private Lessons
training.description:
Customized training designed exclusively for you and your dog. Our professional trainers create structured, goal-driven sessions that build confidence, strengthen communication, and deliver real-world results — all in a safe, controlled setting.

For pricing or to sign up, email training@meadowridgepetlodge.com

team.name: Delaney Hefty
team.bio:
After an exhaustive search for the perfect fit for the position, we’re excited to announce that Delaney Hefty has officially accepted the role of Training Manager at Meadow Ridge Pet Lodge!

Delaney joins us from Paws Pet Resort, in Sioux Falls, one of the highest-rated and most respected pet resorts anywhere in South Dakota. Her experience, passion for animals, and commitment to positive, effective training make her an incredible addition to the Meadow Ridge family.

We’re thrilled to welcome her aboard and can’t wait for our community (and all the pups!) to meet her. Big things are ahead as we continue building Rapid City’s premier destination for training, boarding, daycare, and more.

team.name: Brenna Longden
team.bio:
We are thrilled to announce that Brenna Longden of Grooming by Brenna is officially joining the Meadow Ridge family as our Grooming Manager! 

In the coming weeks her social media page will be merged with ours.

Brenna brings with her a wealth of experience, an impeccable reputation, and a true passion for caring for pets. Her years of dedication at Grooming by Brenna have shown not only her skill but also her heart for making every pet look and feel their best.

As we continue to grow Meadow Ridge Pet Lodge into a place “Where Pets Feel at Home”, Brenna will be leading our grooming team to new heights—helping us deliver the highest level of care and service to all our furry guests in the Rapid City area!

Please join us in giving Brenna a warm Meadow Ridge welcome in the comments below. We couldn’t be more excited for what’s ahead!

faqs.q: Are dogs allowed in the tap room and indoor / outdoor social areas?
faqs.a: Yes! Well behaved dogs are certainly allowed but must remain on leash and controlled at all times.

faqs.q: Are leashes and collars required when bringing my dog or cat into the lobby for daycare or boarding
faqs.a: Yes, please always have your dog or cat on a leash and with collar when at Meadow Ridge.  This is for the safety of all guests and animals.

faqs.q: Are the Splash Parks open for Walk Ins?
faqs.a: We've heard you but at this time the splash parks are only available for a $5.00 add on to boarding or daycare for splash park fun for your pup!  We do plan on opening them up for walk-in later this Summer / 2026.  Stay tuned!

faqs.q: How does your annual popcorn bucket work?
faqs.a: We have theatre quality popcorn in The Dog House Social area!  Even better we have an annual popcorn bucket program!  For just $9.99 your bucket w/ lid is valid for 1 year!  This entitles you to a bucket full of fresh hot buttered popcorn at purchase and $1.99 plus tax refills all year!  Even better - you get FREE refills with any purchase on Saturdays!

faqs.q: Do you have a child play area?
faqs.a: Coming Summer of 2026 we are adding a full fenced in child pay set area on the property!

faqs.q: Are add-ons available for Daycare or Boarding?
faqs.a: Yes!  You will be given options at the time you book your reservation!

faqs.q: What is the difference from the regular boarding kennels and the VIP Presidential Suites?
faqs.a: All of our boarding suites are spacious, but our Presidential Suites, while different sizes are at least 5'x7' and give your furry loved one their own private walled suite, some with windows, and all have a tv which you can have us play what you want on them!  Each VIP wing has their own outdoor play and break areas!

faqs.q: How much is your 24/7 self-wash and who can use it?
faqs.a:
The 24/7 wash is available for single washes while we are open for just $20 or 24/7 access is granted to our monthly subscription members for just $50 per month! 

Subscription offers unlimited washes for all dogs the member has registered at Meadow Ridge Pet Lodge.  All dogs in the self wash MUST be registered at Meadow Ridge Pet lodge with current vaccinations.
